## Limitations

The exploration of free will is inherently complex, involving interdisciplinary perspectives from philosophy, neuroscience, and psychology. The conclusions drawn from scientific studies are often subject to interpretation and debate. Additionally, the philosophical arguments are deeply rooted in subjective interpretations of human experience, making it challenging to reach a definitive conclusion. The ongoing nature of research in this area means that new findings could further influence the understanding of free will in the future.